themagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> My friend finally after a year of coaxing is going to start playing EQ.  I am a 51st level magician, and need to get him caught up to me a bit.  Couple of questions I have are:<br>
<br>
1.  What is in your opinion the best class for him to start?<br>
2.  What is the easiest class for me to power level to the upper 30's?<br>
<br>
Thank you much, I look forward to hearing from you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=glasya>Glasya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#333333>(2/21/01 7:22:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Twink</span><hr size=1> Depends on which items you can twink him with.  If he is new to EQ try a melee type which you can PL easily with a damage shield and get items relatively easily.  If your friend wants some spells try an SK or paladin.  All depends on what your friend likes to do and what type of a character he will fit playing.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucauisthesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cauis the Summoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(2/21/01 9:04:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> He doesn't care what class he wants to play, but he said no melee because he knows I can't heal him.  Basically the classes he pointed out he would like to play (after I told him of the advantages of us working together) are.<br>
<br>
Cleric (healing pet)<br>
Necro (Fear)<br>
Shaman (healing pet and buffs/slows extra pet)<br>
Druid (same thing)<br>
Wizard (Nuking)<br>
Enchanter (Clarity and the likes) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrayel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>grayel</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/01 12:59:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> My personal vote would be a Druid or a Shaman-<br>
<br>
~DRUID~<br>
- Snare (just think of the /pet no taunt kiting)<br>
- TELEPORTS!!<br>
- Heals/Regen<br>
- HP Buffs<br>
- DOT's<br>
- Damage Shields<br>
- Harmony for single pulling outdoors<br>
- SoW<br>
<br>
~SHAMAN~<br>
- Slow line<br>
- HP Buffs<br>
- Heals/Regen<br>
- Debuffs<br>
- Attack (speed) buffs<br>
- SoW<br>
- Secondary (weaker) pet<br>
<br>
Just some things to consider.  Personally I think the Druid gets the edge due to the Teleport's and Evacs... changing hunting grounds quickly and reducing travel time is an enormously underrated benefit.  Additionally, being able to evac from a bad scenario and NOT losing that hard won experience is invaluable as well.<br>
 <p>Mystic Grayel <BR>
