1 tactic that i have found is nice is to have the cleric keep me healed while i use my 51 aoe spell to wiped out anything around me..its nice doing 4 spectres at once with this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/01 2:17:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'd say that a necro is the best overall partner and the easiest to powerlevel.<br>
<br>
This doesn't mean that other classes aren't worthwhile.. a cleric/mage combo can take anything a necro/mage combo can (and perhaps more), druid/mage combos and shaman/mage combos are also very good.  (Hell, SK/Mage combos are fierce too. Malice mob, let SK darkness-fear) <br>
<br>
Necros are good because their skills match with a Magicians quite nicely.  Darkness-Fear with two pets is one mean ole tactic.  Necros can also provide mez and heal as well as some other nice skills.   Also, a Necro is extremely easy for a Magician to powerlevel.   Dmg shield pet, Necro uses lvl 1 lifetap to pull (makes sure he does do damage), and then just heals his pet as our 25pt damage shield eats the MoB alive.   <br>
<br>
Once you get him up to about 38th lvl or so (forget when he gets xp) you can take him to Mines of Nurga.  Go in to where theres a nice room with lots of MoBs.  Whipe it out with Magician (get xp for Necro) and then let Necro *without a pet* outside of the group take a Mob or two until out of mana (get full xp with dungeon xp bonus) and then group him up and let Mage pet mow down stuff until he regens mana.  You can blast someone up to 45 in record time like that.  <br>
<br>
Clerics,Shamans and Druids would all be good to PL as well because you have the dmgshield + heal capability.   Like I said, those classes mix with Magicians very well.<br>
<br>
Enchanters are also fun to play alongside of as well.  You don't get the full range of skills/power that you get with the other groups, but instead of taking harder MoBs you can take a lot more of easier MoBs.   They can be easily powerleveled by having the magician knock something down to a sliver and then having the Enchanter mem blur it and finish it off.   <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquezzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quezzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/01 8:41:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> The fastest leveling combo would be a Halfling Druid.  That is also a good combo with a Mage.  And, you get SoW and a personal transportation unit as well! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
