</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umatches475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Matches475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/01 10:44:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> I agree to the fact that rogues or monks make great partners for mages.  The reason most ppl were saying necros, clerics, chanters... was because that is what the friend wanted to play.  Towards the top of the post he gave a list and everyone was kind of picking from that.  <br>
<br>
If it wasn't for that list, I would say that a Ranger would make a great choice as well.  They get Druid and Shaman buffs (some of them) and they have dual wield and double attack.  An earth pet with Feet of Cat cast on it, is a much better pet because the entire agi problem is solved.  The fireshielded Earth pet with Feet of the Cat, Strength of the Earth, and whatever of the Skin series they have cast on it will destroy just about any mob that you want using the pull on pet tactic.  (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showMessage?topicID=6.topic)">pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagi...D=6.topic)</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/01 2:16:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician Partner question?!?!</span><hr size=1> Heh.. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> class can work well with a magician. Even another magician is a good partner. You just have to play smart and use both of the classes abilities as best as possible. Just ask your friend to pick a class that he <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> wants</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to play, and I'm sure you guys will kick butt and find some awesome tactics that work well with your two-person team.<br>
<br>
Since you did ask for suggestions, however, I will give mine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  DRUID. A magician by himself can nuke like a half-wizard, and tank through his pet (basically). The druid, especially at higher levels, can heal you and your pet. The druid can also snare, making kills safer since the mobs won't run away when they're low on life. He can also SoW, to make it easier to go between zones, and to make hunting much safer. Also, he can port, and the ports will cut your travel time by 90% in most cases.<br>
<br>
Other good partners are an enchanter (mez, clarity, and enc pet), and shaman (slow, shaman pet, sow, and others). I would certainly go with Druid though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>Mard Kirn - 51 Druid (Prexus)<BR>
